        <body>
           <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl" resp="#NW">
            <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl" resp="#NW">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/>LUGUQRIT MA[QI] | QRITT[I] 
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
               <p>of Luccreth son of Creth</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
               <p>Compound of Lug and -creth (McManus 1991, 103), cp. CIIC 68. Kilcaskan, Cork (LUGUQRIT [ ... ] LONAS); CIIC 207. Kilcoolaght II, Kerry ( [ ... ]]ECC MAQI L[UGUQ]RRIT); CIIC 57. Greenhill I, Cork (TRENU MAQI MUCOI QRITTI) - Crothrige? (McManus 1991, p 111).</p>
               <p>Labialised guttural /kw/ preserved in QRIT(TI), related to <foreign xml:lang="ga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/13271">cruth</ref></foreign> 'form' (McManus 1991, 121).</p>
               <p>McManus (1991, p 113) notes this inscription as an example of the repetition of an element of the father's name in the son's.</p>
            </div>
